<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
A piece of land is in the shape of a triangle. Two sides measure <m>{10}</m> m and <m>{13}</m> m, and the angle between them is <m>{50}</m>°. Find the area of the land.
</p>

<p>
Give your answer correct to <alert>2 decimal places</alert>.
</p>

<p>
Area = <fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/> <m>\text{cm}^2</m>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Step 1: Use the formula:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = \frac{1}{2}ab\sin C
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Substitute the values:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = \frac{1}{2} \times {10} \times {13} \times \sin {50}^\circ
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Evaluate:
</p>

<p>
<me>
A = {49.79}\text{ m}^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the area of the land is <m>{49.79}</m> <m>\text{cm}^2</m>.
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>49.79</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>